---
title: "How to Use a Daily Dashboard Review as a High-ROI Organizational Habit"
date: "2024-02-21"
summary: "Use a daily dashboard review as a high-ROI habit. Five minutes at the start of every day produces outsized returns."
coverImage: ""
tags:
  - "Habit Systems"
author: "Redevise"
---

The team logs in. They start working. They do not check the dashboard until something goes wrong. The dashboard is reactive. It should be proactive.

A daily dashboard review is a five-minute habit at the start of every day. The team looks at the dashboard. They note the exceptions. They plan their day around the exceptions.

Here is why the ROI is high.

The review takes five minutes. The exceptions found in those five minutes determine the next eight hours. Without the review, the team discovers exceptions when they become problems. With the review, the team discovers them when they are still solvable.

In our client engagements at Redevise, we regularly design and deploy these solutions. For example, when partnering with a fast-growing team in 2024, we implemented a daily dashboard review. The team of eight people started spending five minutes every morning reviewing the dashboard. The time spent on firefighting dropped 40 percent. The team was solving problems before they became fires.

The habit cost five minutes a day. The return was hours of avoided firefighting per week.

The teams that skip the review are the ones that spend the day reacting. The teams that review are the ones that spend the day acting.

Start the day with five minutes. Check the dashboard. Note the exceptions. Plan the day. The ROI compounds.
